- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a methodology for improving the extraction of choreographies, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with the behavior of concurrent components, which is a topic in programming languages. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper captures programs that work by exploiting asynchronous communication, which is a topic in distributed computing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions time complexity improvements in the proposed methodology, which is a topic in algorithms.
